# What is the Kernel?

Heart of the operating system. Hardware and software communicate with each other via Kernel.

## What is the purpose of _Kernel_ ?

It manages the hardware like CPU, memory and disk.
Programs safely connect to hardware thanks to the Kernel.

# What is the Process?

A running program.

## What is the purpose of _Process_ ?

It provides the memory area and resources for each program.

# What is the Thread?

The smallest running unit in the process.

## What is the purpose of _Thread_ ?

It provides parallel processes in the same program.

# What is the Memory Management?

It allocates the RAM in program each other with safely and regularly.

# What is the CPU Schedulers?

It decides which process or thread runs and when.

## What is the purpose of _CPU_?

It uses the CPU fairly and efficiently.
It enables to run multiple-program.
